[thinking] I'm exploring generating CRT and how the RSAPrivateKeySpec class might return RSAPrivateCrtKeySpec. If I check the RSAPrivateKeySpec.class first in the RSAKeyFactory engine, would it point to the CRT spec? It seems like if spec.isAssignableFrom(RSAPrivateCrtKeySpec.class) is true, it should. There’s a possibility small sizes might lead to issues in recording, and I'm wondering if KeyUtils.validatedModulus rejects small moduli. Overall, I need to ensure my serialization process doesn't get too complex or recursive.
