[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing RSA Key Generation**\n\nI'm exploring generating CRT and how the RSAPrivateKeySpec class might return RSAPrivateCrtKeySpec. If I check the RSAPrivateKeySpec.class first in the RSAKeyFactory engine, would it point to the CRT spec? It seems like if spec.isAssignableFrom(RSAPrivateCrtKeySpec.class) is true, it should. There’s a possibility small sizes might lead to issues in recording, and I'm wondering if KeyUtils.validatedModulus rejects small moduli. Overall, I need to ensure my serialization process doesn't get too complex or recursive.\n\n**Considering serialization options**\n\nI’m thinking we can change the `writeUsingSerializationHook` to return a `List<Object>` instead of a `byte[]`. I guess this could make it easier for the read hook to process the data. It feels like a straightforward adjustment that could enhance how data is handled. I’ll need to explore how this change affects downstream components and ensure it all integrates smoothly. It's interesting how small changes can have bigger implications on the overall functionality!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f337405c7c49118016a3fb5b1a19081978b520809c1c90631\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP7XErT7PMp2AdAqM6Kx0qonMLMS7xHYOYWOASBSmTdKAb2ekQC-jTlIF4cIwOXq_oLiVGCZdBPaGcKgBgjxur5zexXRDMXP4ypB0Q-zEjxxEhNu_2B1SzolUaQazaL-QUrPq11cLC_AAoYz5WUH-lIkEuddJFtPMhadi_LZW6IckLaVnuK9INwjOluESGW6Pt3HSl6Zh0lfAJdxwY3JdW4LRjpwW14U-1ND1EZoV1kJv0rr2p1TcB_biHLYbVnds3wiXo3WIs9K4SZleuuA-yd1SnDAS49WPwYVfDDLSyoIm0BJ0WqGZAFtU6VGHLWIFUtWgJ5GivqToh1TghNO5GdmUorEnS-OAJeOLwZwxzuTNZfTepUx3ZKOVQ5uzSnj2jLE9_y19EriNW7k9DB3z4Fv8JAdS9OLZMgnR-p6kdXXo4rW4Kp1i2Uavwr8Wbnlr-hSttNvg_hlTWD98yDZEwVFiZP2f4JtJ9UvW0v0Tbk9xS3Mfk3VpRC3qXkx80YjDdpKfDvRiwGj5GEkacM12RbcENsiifl8apNUJj-X3Lt5SQ_8OdYEhPncQMBNi0MIjM7Hc5aHw4GeJjp7Lxu978TuTEXTvcGl50dwFYHuOLAVDZ9H8KWbo-2ja_313qIXq-qDbe-U2MPOY6RfaFeDe-lC8It